267
00:21:36,129 --> 00:21:39,174
Yes, she is here,
and she is waiting for you!

268
00:21:39,215 --> 00:21:42,677
She's not waiting for me,
she's waiting for you.

269
00:21:42,719 --> 00:21:44,846
Are you coming?

270
00:21:44,888 --> 00:21:48,350
No! I'm playing cards!

271
00:21:48,391 --> 00:21:52,187
You're not coming?

272
00:21:52,479 --> 00:21:56,566
Get over here, Dalby!

273
00:22:07,911 --> 00:22:12,457
Look, I'm sorry about
the misunderstanding.

274
00:22:12,499 --> 00:22:15,126
Joel, be a courageous person.
Open the door!

275
00:22:15,168 --> 00:22:18,546
That way, you see, I can call a cab.

276
00:22:18,588 --> 00:22:20,715
Again, I'm really sorry.

277
00:22:20,757 --> 00:22:24,636
As long as we come to an arrangement,
I'm in no mood for complaining.

278
00:22:24,678 --> 00:22:27,389
I mean, when you put
your good money down...

279
00:22:27,430 --> 00:22:30,725
...you gotta get what you wanted
in the first place. Know what I mean?

280
00:22:30,767 --> 00:22:35,480
When you buy a TV,
you don't buy Sony if you want RCA.

281
00:22:35,522 --> 00:22:38,066
I know we could get along
real well. But, hey!

282
00:22:38,108 --> 00:22:41,236
It's your hard-earned money, right?

283
00:22:41,277 --> 00:22:44,989
This way, we make an arrangement
and everyone is satisfied.

284
00:22:45,031 --> 00:22:46,408
You had carfare.

285
00:22:46,449 --> 00:22:50,578
A long ride. I don't ever come out this far.

286
00:22:50,620 --> 00:22:51,746
And your time.

287
00:22:51,788 --> 00:22:55,041
My time, my effort,
my infinite patience and understanding.

288
00:22:55,083 --> 00:22:56,167
Thank you.

289
00:22:56,209 --> 00:22:58,628
$75.

290
00:22:59,212 --> 00:23:00,255
Fair enough.

291
00:23:00,296 --> 00:23:03,466
Joel, I'm going to give you a number.

292
00:23:03,508 --> 00:23:06,052
You ask for Lana.

293
00:23:06,094 --> 00:23:10,223
- It's what you want.
- Thank you.

294
00:23:10,265 --> 00:23:16,771
It's what every white boy
off the lake wants.

295
00:23:44,799 --> 00:23:48,011
All right, Goodson,
we know you're in there!

296
00:23:48,053 --> 00:23:50,347
What's that?

297
00:23:50,388 --> 00:23:55,185
I think someone's out there.

298
00:23:59,064 --> 00:24:02,275
Joel, the house is surrounded.

299
00:24:02,317 --> 00:24:05,779
Do exactly as we say,
and no one gets hurt.

300
00:24:05,820 --> 00:24:06,863
Oh, shit!

301
00:24:06,905 --> 00:24:16,414
Get off the babysitter! Put on your
pants, and come out with your hands up!

302
00:24:18,750 --> 00:24:22,337
Please, Joel, do as they say!

303
00:24:22,379 --> 00:24:24,130
Get off the babysitter!

304
00:24:24,172 --> 00:24:28,802
Don't throw your life away like this.

305
00:24:28,843 --> 00:24:34,474
Listen, you goddamn punk, you'll never
have a future! Not if I can help it!

306
00:24:34,516 --> 00:24:37,310
You got that? No future!

307
00:24:37,352 --> 00:24:39,062
Who is that?

308
00:24:39,104 --> 00:24:42,107
My father!

309
00:25:37,245 --> 00:25:40,040
Hello? Lana?

310
00:25:40,081 --> 00:25:42,459
Yes?

311
00:25:42,500 --> 00:25:44,794
Hi.

312
00:25:56,598 --> 00:25:59,142
I'm a nice guy,
and I'd like to meet you tonight.

313
00:25:59,184 --> 00:26:03,188
Fine. Where are you?

314
00:26:03,855 --> 00:26:07,650
Where do you live?

315
00:26:09,361 --> 00:26:11,404
Glencoe.

316
00:26:11,446 --> 00:26:15,158
What's your name?

317
00:26:18,536 --> 00:26:20,580
Ralph.

318
00:26:20,622 --> 00:26:25,627
Ralph, can I have the address?

319
00:26:29,464 --> 00:26:32,050
345...

320
00:26:32,509 --> 00:26:34,928
...Remson.

321
00:26:34,969 --> 00:26:37,555
Ralph?

322
00:26:38,890 --> 00:26:42,977
I'll see you tonight.

323
00:28:21,034 --> 00:28:25,830
Are you ready for me, Ralph?

324
00:30:22,113 --> 00:30:26,076
This is a beautiful place, Ralph.
Is it all yours?

325
00:30:26,117 --> 00:30:28,745
It's my folks', actually.

326
00:30:28,787 --> 00:30:32,957
Do you know what it's worth?

327
00:30:32,999 --> 00:30:34,292
A lot, probably.

328
00:30:34,334 --> 00:30:36,294
Oh, yeah! Real estate?

329
00:30:36,336 --> 00:30:38,421
It's fabulous!

330
00:30:38,463 --> 00:30:44,552
Look, Lana... my name really isn't Ralph.

331
00:30:45,178 --> 00:30:47,806
It's Joel.

332
00:30:47,847 --> 00:30:51,851
I need $300... Joel.

333
00:30:52,811 --> 00:30:53,978
You're kidding?

334
00:30:54,020 --> 00:30:55,647
No, I don't believe I am.

335
00:30:55,689 --> 00:30:59,776
Can I send it to you?

336
00:31:00,360 --> 00:31:02,821
Can you send it to me, Joel?

337
00:31:02,862 --> 00:31:06,658
I just don't have that much here
in the house.

338
00:31:06,700 --> 00:31:09,452
How much do you have?

339
00:31:09,494 --> 00:31:12,414
- I have $50.
- $50?

340
00:31:12,455 --> 00:31:17,961
What are we going to do about this?

341
00:31:20,839 --> 00:31:22,507
I have a bond at the bank I could cash...

342
00:31:22,549 --> 00:31:26,136
I'm not good at waiting for people.

343
00:31:26,177 --> 00:31:27,846
I'll be quick.

344
00:31:27,887 --> 00:31:31,307
Give it a try.

345
00:32:09,095 --> 00:32:12,015
I'm back!

346
00:32:23,485 --> 00:32:27,197
I'm here for you.

347
00:32:45,590 --> 00:32:48,051
How could she? It's so stupid!

348
00:32:48,093 --> 00:32:49,552
Tell your mother it broke!

349
00:32:49,594 --> 00:32:53,223
That egg is worth a lot more than $300!

350
00:32:53,264 --> 00:32:55,558
What are you going to do?

351
00:32:55,600 --> 00:32:57,936
I'm gonna get it back,
is what I'm gonna do.

352
00:32:57,977 --> 00:32:58,770
Are you going to help?

353
00:32:58,812 --> 00:33:01,731
Sure. When?

354
00:33:01,773 --> 00:33:03,066
Right now!

355
00:33:03,108 --> 00:33:06,945
I can't do it right now!
I have a trig. Mid-term tomorrow!

356
00:33:06,986 --> 00:33:08,446
Hey, "Mr. What-The-Fuck"...

357
00:33:08,488 --> 00:33:10,949
...what about "exploring
the dark side" and all that?

358
00:33:10,990 --> 00:33:13,243
Or was that just bullshit?

359
00:33:13,284 --> 00:33:16,955
That was just bullshit, Joel.

360
00:33:16,996 --> 00:33:22,293
I'm surprised you listened to me.

361
00:33:25,005 --> 00:33:28,508
Are you coming?

362
00:33:35,140 --> 00:33:38,810
How can you even tell if she'll be here?

363
00:33:38,852 --> 00:33:43,106
I called Jackie and she said to try here.

364
00:33:43,148 --> 00:33:49,112
Great idea. Where else could
we get a hot chocolate for $4?

365
00:33:49,154 --> 00:33:51,698
She's here!

366
00:33:51,740 --> 00:33:53,950
Where?

367
00:33:53,992 --> 00:33:57,996
The blue dress... those legs...

368
00:33:58,038 --> 00:33:59,289
That's her.

369
00:33:59,330 --> 00:34:02,917
She's fantastic!

370
00:34:10,884 --> 00:34:15,472
She's looking right at us!

371
00:34:21,561 --> 00:34:25,648
She knows we're here.

372
00:34:33,365 --> 00:34:35,617
That's it?

373
00:34:35,658 --> 00:34:39,245
That's it, Joel?

374
00:34:40,205 --> 00:34:45,210
I can't believe we came
all the way here for that!

375
00:34:45,251 --> 00:34:47,379
At least she knows we're on to her, Miles.

376
00:34:47,420 --> 00:34:49,339
Yeah, she must be terrified.

377
00:34:49,381 --> 00:34:51,883
Joel!

378
00:34:54,260 --> 00:34:56,554
Is this your car?

379
00:34:56,596 --> 00:34:59,182
Maybe.

380
00:34:59,557 --> 00:35:01,685
Could we talk a minute?

381
00:35:01,726 --> 00:35:03,645
Okay.

382
00:35:03,687 --> 00:35:05,188
Let's talk!

383
00:35:05,230 --> 00:35:11,528
Okay. In the car, all right? It's freezing.

384
00:35:19,619 --> 00:35:22,414
Will you do me a favor?

385
00:35:22,455 --> 00:35:24,416
You want me to do you a favor?

386
00:35:24,457 --> 00:35:25,792
I just need a lift.

387
00:35:25,834 --> 00:35:30,338
Look, I want my egg back!

388
00:35:30,588 --> 00:35:31,798
Get out of the car!

389
00:35:31,840 --> 00:35:33,216
Joel, better get moving.

390
00:35:33,258 --> 00:35:34,718
I want my egg back!

391
00:35:34,759 --> 00:35:36,636
You got it, all right? Just start driving!

392
00:35:36,678 --> 00:35:38,054
When?

393
00:35:38,096 --> 00:35:40,306
- Now!
- Open the door!

394
00:35:40,348 --> 00:35:41,558
When do I get it back?

395
00:35:41,599 --> 00:35:42,851
Start driving!

396
00:35:42,892 --> 00:35:45,562
Open the door!
Are you going to open the door?

397
00:35:45,603 --> 00:35:47,188
Hey, buster!

398
00:35:47,230 --> 00:35:48,106
Fuck! Will you just...

399
00:35:48,148 --> 00:35:50,233
- Get off the car!
- Just start driving!

400
00:35:50,275 --> 00:35:53,236
Start driving, now!

401
00:35:53,278 --> 00:35:56,406
Why don't you start the car, Joel?

402
00:35:56,448 --> 00:35:57,907
Fuck! Get out of here!

403
00:35:57,949 --> 00:36:00,243
Start the goddamn car, Joel!

404
00:36:00,285 --> 00:36:03,913
Lana, open the door.

405
00:36:03,955 --> 00:36:05,915
Where are you going? Lana!

406
00:36:05,957 --> 00:36:10,545
Get out, or I'll kill you!

407
00:36:19,137 --> 00:36:20,764
Who was that guy?

408
00:36:20,805 --> 00:36:22,724
My manager.

409
00:36:22,766 --> 00:36:26,353
He gets a little crazy sometimes.

410
00:36:26,394 --> 00:36:30,440
This is my friend, Miles.

411
00:36:30,482 --> 00:36:32,776
Do you like excitement, Miles?

412
00:36:32,817 --> 00:36:35,612
Love it.

413
00:36:51,544 --> 00:36:54,297
Okay, where do you want to go?

414
00:36:54,339 --> 00:36:57,676
I don't know, Joel.
I haven't given it a lot of thought.

415
00:36:57,717 --> 00:36:59,135
Tell me this:

416
00:36:59,177 --> 00:37:03,306
Am I going in the right direction?

417
00:37:03,348 --> 00:37:05,392
Oh, shit! Here he comes!

418
00:37:05,433 --> 00:37:07,310
Here who comes?

419
00:37:07,352 --> 00:37:11,064
That manager guy?

420
00:37:13,024 --> 00:37:14,526
Hey, Guido!

421
00:37:14,567 --> 00:37:17,153
Big man, Guido!

422
00:37:17,195 --> 00:37:18,822
Big man with a gun!

423
00:37:18,863 --> 00:37:20,156
What are you going to do?

424
00:37:20,198 --> 00:37:24,285
Shoot us all? Stupid!

425
00:37:26,371 --> 00:37:28,498
This guy Guido...

426
00:37:28,540 --> 00:37:31,501
...he's a "manager"?
- That's right.

427
00:37:31,543 --> 00:37:32,836
Or a pimp?

428
00:37:32,877 --> 00:37:34,921
Now, that's quick, Joel.

429
00:37:34,963 --> 00:37:37,841
Have you always been this quick,
or is this something new?

430
00:37:37,882 --> 00:37:39,509
I don't believe this!

431
00:37:39,551 --> 00:37:41,219
I have a trig. Mid-term tomorrow...

432
00:37:41,261 --> 00:37:48,268
...and I'm being chased by Guido,
The Killer Pimp!

433
00:38:09,581 --> 00:38:12,042
Miles?

434
00:38:12,083 --> 00:38:13,168
I think I can take him.

435
00:38:13,209 --> 00:38:17,505
What are you talking...

436
00:38:45,158 --> 00:38:50,038
I'm really not enjoying this.

437
00:39:07,305 --> 00:39:12,310
I think I'm going to throw up.

438
00:39:18,692 --> 00:39:24,989
I think I'm going to throw up on you, Joel!

439
00:39:43,341 --> 00:39:44,843
Porsche...

440
00:39:44,884 --> 00:39:49,472
...there is no substitute.

441
00:39:49,597 --> 00:39:52,517
Fuck you.

442
00:39:55,311 --> 00:39:57,272
Hi, dear. It's Mother.

443
00:39:57,313 --> 00:39:58,648
How are you?

444
00:39:58,690 --> 00:40:01,192
Just checking in to say hello,
see how you're doing...

445
00:40:01,234 --> 00:40:05,363
...and give you our flight information.

446
00:40:05,405 --> 00:40:09,492
Wait a minute. Let me write this down.

447
00:40:09,534 --> 00:40:14,205
Saturday, United, Flight 162 at 3:30.

448
00:40:14,247 --> 00:40:19,169
That's right. How's everything else?
Do you have enough money?

449
00:40:19,210 --> 00:40:24,090
It never seems to go as far
as you think it will.

450
00:40:24,132 --> 00:40:26,051
Yes, I know.

451
00:40:26,092 --> 00:40:29,554
I'm learning, Mom.

452
00:40:29,596 --> 00:40:33,308
How is Aunt Tudi?

453
00:40:35,643 --> 00:40:38,063
I will.

454
00:40:38,104 --> 00:40:41,900
See you then, bye.

455
00:40:42,067 --> 00:40:44,694
Your folks?

456
00:40:44,736 --> 00:40:46,529
So, how are they?

457
00:40:46,571 --> 00:40:48,365
Oh, they're just great.

458
00:40:48,406 --> 00:40:50,033
How about Aunt Tudi?

459
00:40:50,075 --> 00:40:56,373
Her hip is much better.
She sends her love.

460
00:40:58,291 --> 00:41:00,627
You were telling me about Guido.

461
00:41:00,669 --> 00:41:03,963
I quit Guido.

462
00:41:04,589 --> 00:41:07,509
How come?

463
00:41:10,470 --> 00:41:13,723
He thought he owned me.

464
00:41:13,765 --> 00:41:17,268
Nobody owns me.

465
00:41:18,978 --> 00:41:22,649
The problem is, I owe him for clothes
and hospital bills.

466
00:41:22,691 --> 00:41:25,902
You were in the hospital?

467
00:41:25,944 --> 00:41:28,279
I had this...

468
00:41:28,321 --> 00:41:29,614
...pain in my chest.

469
00:41:29,656 --> 00:41:33,785
I thought it was a heart condition.

470
00:41:33,827 --> 00:41:35,245
What was it?

471
00:41:35,286 --> 00:41:37,414
The doctor said nerves.

472
00:41:37,455 --> 00:41:39,791
Nice service.

473
00:41:39,833 --> 00:41:43,253
Reed & Barton.

474
00:41:44,004 --> 00:41:48,800
Thank you for breakfast. It was good.

475
00:41:48,842 --> 00:41:53,221
I'm going to school now.

476
00:41:56,099 --> 00:42:01,104
I'll have to ask you to leave.

477
00:42:01,771 --> 00:42:03,982
I'm sorry.

478
00:42:04,024 --> 00:42:06,818
You won't let me stay?

479
00:42:06,860 --> 00:42:11,573
No, I have to go to school.

480
00:42:13,366 --> 00:42:17,078
I'm really sorry.

481
00:42:19,372 --> 00:42:22,792
No, I'm sorry.

482
00:42:26,254 --> 00:42:30,175
I'll be right back.

483
00:42:31,134 --> 00:42:33,720
You guys go ahead without me.

484
00:42:33,762 --> 00:42:35,096
She's still here?

485
00:42:35,138 --> 00:42:38,725
She won't leave.

486
00:42:40,143 --> 00:42:43,730
She won't leave.

487
00:42:46,983 --> 00:42:49,527
Lana, look...

488
00:42:49,569 --> 00:42:53,531
...I just want my egg back.
I want my house back.

489
00:42:53,573 --> 00:42:57,619
I have a lot of work to do.

490
00:42:57,660 --> 00:43:03,249
Did you have a good time last night?

491
00:43:03,416 --> 00:43:06,628
You mean when we got back here?

492
00:43:06,670 --> 00:43:11,549
I think you know what I mean.

493
00:43:15,095 --> 00:43:19,015
I had a great time.

494
00:43:20,183 --> 00:43:24,771
Don't tell me I owe you another $300.

495
00:43:24,813 --> 00:43:29,401
Did I say you owe me anything?

496
00:43:29,442 --> 00:43:30,151
No, you didn't.

497
00:43:30,193 --> 00:43:36,574
I don't remember saying
you owe me anything.

498
00:43:38,952 --> 00:43:41,663
What about my mother's egg?

499
00:43:41,705 --> 00:43:49,295
You're the one who's going to college,
you figure it out.

500
00:43:49,337 --> 00:43:51,089
How much time do you need?

501
00:43:51,131 --> 00:43:54,092
I need long enough
to make a few phone calls.

502
00:43:54,134 --> 00:43:56,845
I have to figure out how
to get my stuff back.

503
00:43:56,886 --> 00:44:00,515
Guido has probably locked me
out of the apartment by now.

504
00:44:00,557 --> 00:44:03,518
All right!

505
00:44:03,560 --> 00:44:05,854
But will you do me a favor?

506
00:44:05,895 --> 00:44:09,315
Anything, cookie.

507
00:44:09,357 --> 00:44:13,445
Don't steal anything!

508
00:44:13,862 --> 00:44:17,866
If I come back here,
and find anything missing...

509
00:44:17,907 --> 00:44:21,870
...l'm going straight to the police.
I'm not joking!

510
00:44:21,911 --> 00:44:27,792
Joel, go to school. Go learn something.

511
00:44:39,429 --> 00:44:43,141
May I see your pass, please!

512
00:44:43,183 --> 00:44:46,895
I'm sure you've all read
chapters six through eight...

513
00:44:46,936 --> 00:44:49,481
...so here's a little pop quiz to confirm it.

514
00:44:49,522 --> 00:44:56,029
Will you put your books on the floor,
please?

515
00:45:15,048 --> 00:45:16,383
You didn't tell anyone, did you?

516
00:45:16,424 --> 00:45:18,385
No. Glenn knows.

517
00:45:18,426 --> 00:45:19,594
What about Barry?

518
00:45:19,636 --> 00:45:21,179
He knows, too.

519
00:45:21,221 --> 00:45:23,264
Don't tell anyone!

520
00:45:23,306 --> 00:45:27,018
I won't! I won't!

521
00:45:34,484 --> 00:45:38,780
Lab reports should be on my desk
by tomorrow afternoon.

522
00:45:38,822 --> 00:45:44,536
I won't accept any that aren't typed.

523
00:45:56,506 --> 00:45:58,800
Term papers are due on Friday.

524
00:45:58,842 --> 00:46:03,722
They count for 50%
of this semester's grades.

525
00:46:03,763 --> 00:46:06,558
Damn it!

526
00:46:14,524 --> 00:46:15,734
Hey, Miles, what's going on?

527
00:46:15,775 --> 00:46:17,569
I'm waiting for Glenn.

528
00:46:17,610 --> 00:46:18,945
Glenn? Where is he?

529
00:46:18,987 --> 00:46:20,739
Inside.

530
00:46:20,780 --> 00:46:22,073
In the house?

531
00:46:22,115 --> 00:46:25,952
He wanted to meet her!

532
00:46:25,994 --> 00:46:27,078
What are you doing?

533
00:46:27,120 --> 00:46:28,163
I was inside.

534
00:46:28,204 --> 00:46:31,708
I can see that.

535
00:46:32,542 --> 00:46:34,502
You're home now.

536
00:46:34,544 --> 00:46:39,257
Yeah, I live here, remember?

537
00:46:39,299 --> 00:46:41,885
