01:32:33,595 --> 01:32:35,430
No...

1071
01:32:35,472 --> 01:32:37,724
...I don't think so.

1072
01:32:37,766 --> 01:32:43,813
I just got off the telephone
with Bill Rutherford.

1073
01:32:43,855 --> 01:32:49,861
Apparently, you two had quite a meeting.

1074
01:32:51,613 --> 01:32:55,992
"Princeton can use a guy like Joel."

1075
01:32:56,034 --> 01:32:57,410
What?

1076
01:32:57,452 --> 01:33:01,414
"Princeton can use a guy like Joel."

1077
01:33:01,456 --> 01:33:05,001
His exact words!

1078
01:33:05,043 --> 01:33:06,670
That's unbelievable!

1079
01:33:06,711 --> 01:33:08,838
You're as good as in!

1080
01:33:08,880 --> 01:33:10,674
I knew you could do it!

1081
01:33:10,715 --> 01:33:13,510
Haven't I been telling you,
sometimes you have to say:

1082
01:33:13,551 --> 01:33:16,012
"What the heck!" Take some chances.

1083
01:33:16,054 --> 01:33:17,681
You were so right.

1084
01:33:17,722 --> 01:33:22,310
You've made me very proud.

1085
01:33:25,563 --> 01:33:28,441
I was just thinking...

1086
01:33:28,483 --> 01:33:33,530
...where we might be ten years from now.

1087
01:33:33,571 --> 01:33:35,573
You know what I think?

1088
01:33:35,615 --> 01:33:38,034
I think we're both going to make it big!

1089
01:33:38,076 --> 01:33:43,164
I'm very optimistic! I mean it!

1090
01:33:44,833 --> 01:33:49,212
Can I ask you something?

1091
01:33:51,423 --> 01:33:55,927
Was our night together...

1092
01:33:56,428 --> 01:33:59,222
...just to set up...

1093
01:33:59,264 --> 01:34:03,184
...Vicki and Guido?

1094
01:34:10,233 --> 01:34:12,527
No.

1095
01:34:12,944 --> 01:34:17,073
You don't believe me, do you?

1096
01:34:17,115 --> 01:34:20,160
My name is Russell Bitterman.
I'm from Wheaton High School.

1097
01:34:20,201 --> 01:34:24,914
Our product is a paper-towel
holder that sells for $8.95.

1098
01:34:24,956 --> 01:34:30,837
We made a profit of $850 last semester.

1099
01:34:34,549 --> 01:34:38,762
I don't want you to get hurt.

1100
01:34:38,803 --> 01:34:44,184
My name is Evonne Williams.
We sell decorative planters for $7.

1101
01:34:44,225 --> 01:34:50,106
We made a profit of $500 last semester.

1102
01:34:50,148 --> 01:34:53,443
Guess we won't see each other for awhile.

1103
01:34:53,485 --> 01:34:56,196
I know.

1104
01:34:56,488 --> 01:34:58,198
Are you going straight home now?

1105
01:34:58,239 --> 01:35:00,116
I don't know. Why?

1106
01:35:00,158 --> 01:35:04,788
It might be nice if we spent
the evening together.

1107
01:35:04,829 --> 01:35:07,791
I'd really like that.

1108
01:35:07,832 --> 01:35:11,461
How much have you got on you?

1109
01:35:11,503 --> 01:35:13,088
How much have I got on me?

1110
01:35:13,129 --> 01:35:14,964
I've got $20.

1111
01:35:15,006 --> 01:35:17,217
$20, Lana?

1112
01:35:17,258 --> 01:35:19,469
What are we going to do about this?

1113
01:35:19,511 --> 01:35:23,181
- Can I send it to you?
- Can you send it to me?

1114
01:35:23,223 --> 01:35:25,183
'Cause I don't have that much here.

1115
01:35:25,225 --> 01:35:26,810
How about I write you a check?

1116
01:35:26,851 --> 01:35:31,481
Do you think I'd accept a check from you?
What am I, stupid?

1117
01:35:31,523 --> 01:35:34,818
I have a bond at the bank.

1118
01:35:34,859 --> 01:35:37,487
My name is Joel Goodson.

1119
01:35:37,529 --> 01:35:40,490
I deal in human fulfillment.

1120
01:35:40,532 --> 01:35:44,828
I grossed over $8,000 in one night.

1121
01:35:44,869 --> 01:35:50,083
The time of your life, huh, kid?
